climbs.name: Thugagra
climbs.fa: Equipped by Mike Snyder, 2013, FA:Sasha Digiulian, 2014

content.description: Do a tricky move at the start to a crimp rail. Make your way up pockets and edges, with good rests, to a high crux just before the run to the chains. Some go left, some go right. Great movement all over.
content.location: Immediately to the right of Deez Nutz.

content.description: Link-up. Start on Special Delivery, climbing up onto the pillar and clipping two more bolts. Traverse left onto Hootie Hoo and continue to the top of that route. A nice way to climb on HH without pulling the sharp boulder at the bottom.
content.location: Right side of the Rap Stars wall.

content.description: The beautiful overhanging arete!  This route is pure power endurance - boulder problem, clip, shake, and repeat.  The hardest moves come down low after leaving the comfy ledge, but the route stays on you the whole way.  Sneaky rest around the 11th bolt, although it might feel like cheating...
content.location: Right most route on Rap Stars wall.  Rakkup app. has the best info.

content.description: Link-up. Climb Sniggity and then cut right onto Deez Nutz climbing the last 3 bolts of that route. Flows well and makes for a great warmup.
content.protection: Dozen bolts. Back clean the first few.
content.location: Left side of the Rap Stars wall. Starts in the huge corner. Belay from elevated dirt ledge.

content.description: Work your way up the crack towards the big white horn. Stem your way up, staying inside the dihedral, and managing the pump. Not a gimme!
content.location: Start on the platform within the notch shared with The Buffalo has Landed.

content.description: Start on the far left side of the Rap Star wall. Climb up to a ledge, then wrap around the arete and climb next to Mr. Hyde. Technical but less pumpy than Mr. Hyde or Dr. Jeckyl.
content.location: Around the corner to the right of Mr Hyde, left of Kaleidoscope Eyes.

content.description: A fun route with interesting features and movement: layback, stem, traverse, and pull pockets.
content.protection: 12 bolts to anchors with chains and clips
content.location: This is the middle route on the left side of the wall. From the base, a thin seam leads to a low ledge. Follow the right-facing arc, then up and over a slight roof. Traverse left, then up the white vertical section to anchors.

content.description: Boulder problem between 3rd and 4th draw off the flake. 12bish to the top.
Bouldery start leads to long pulls on decent pockets and edges. Stopper crux at about 1/3 height leads to pumpy jug hauling. Awesome rock climbing!

climbs.name: Deez Nutz
climbs.fa: Established by Mike Snyder, FA: Sasha Digiulian

content.description: Super fun climbing on mostly good edges and pockets. The climbing is relatively sustained, with managing the pump being the "crux".
content.location: Far left of Rap Stars, just before the dihedral crack. Start on the built-up platform in the notch shared with The Buffalo Has Landed.

content.description: Follow the crack system in the corner.
content.location: Left side of the rap star wall, in the corner
